content:

From Monday 13 November until Friday 17 November, lift upgrades will be taking place. During this time there will be no accessible route at Martin Place station. Customers can use Town Hall, St. James or Wynyard stations as an alternative.
If you need help, ask staff or phone 02 9379 4858.

content:
Tuesday 14 November
  • The lift between the Concourse, Platform 4 and Hattersley Street will be unavailable.
  • An accessible route is available using Taylor Avenue, Subway Road and Godfrey Street. For access to your train service, you may need to change trains at Wolli Creek station to complete your journey. 

Wednesday 15 November 
  • The lift between the Concourse to Platform 1 and Railway Street will be unavailable.
  • An accessible route is available using Godfrey Street, Subway Road and Taylor Avenue. For access to your train service, you may need to change trains at Rockdale station to complete your journey.

Thursday 16 November
  • The Lift between the Concourse to Platforms 2 and 3 will be unavailable.
  • To access your train service, you may need to change trains at Rockdale or Wolli Creek stations to complete your journey.

Staff will be available on site to assist anyone with mobility issues, prams or luggage. We apologise for any inconvenience.
subtitle: Banksia Station lift upgrades
